      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V at quasi-static rates; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to tensile coupon data for Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM Grade 23). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient 0.2 used at all interfaces. Model form consistent with prior FDA FEA guidance for spinal implants."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile testing; geometry from CMM-verified CAD; boundary conditions from ASTM F1717 fixture specification.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and tangent modulus obtained from lot-specific tensile testing of three coupons per material lot. Screw and rod geometry verified by coordinate measuring machine to within 0.02 mm. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 loading fixture geometry. Monte Carlo UQ performed across all inputs to characterize output variability, sampling 10,000 realizations from input distributions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
